Intuition
this is a unique question unlike normal 2 pointer question in this question we need to understand backspace deletes a character so instead of traversing string from start we traverse from end , now we traverse both strings from the end because backspace affects previous characters.
We use a skip counter to ignore characters deleted by '#'.
For each string, we find the next valid character by skipping deleted ones.
Then we compare both characters. If at any point they differ, return false.
If both strings finish together, return true.

Approach
i = len(s) -1
j = len (t) - 1
skipS =0
skipT = 0
looping condition while i >= 0 or j >= 0
check valid element of string s , if "#"found increase skip count , skip the chracter and decrease skip count, then check valid character for string t ,

then compare both the valid charcaters fromm string s and t , if notequal return false , if 1 string is completly traverse and other is still remaining return false

after comparing update i and j pointer for comparison of next valid character

return true if all the conditions become true

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(m+n)

Space complexity:
O(1)

Code
class Solution:
    def backspaceCompare(self, s: str, t: str) -> bool:
        i = len(s) - 1
        j = len(t) - 1

        skipS = 0
        skipT = 0

        while i >=0 or j >= 0:

            while i >=0:
                if s[i] == "#":
                    skipS += 1
                    i -= 1
                elif skipS > 0:
                    skipS -= 1
                    i -= 1
                else:
                    break

            while  j >=0:
                if t[j] == "#":
                    skipT += 1
                    j -= 1
                elif skipT > 0:
                    skipT -= 1
                    j -= 1
                else:
                    break
            
            if i >= 0 and j >= 0:
                if s[i] != t[j]:
                    return False
            elif i >=0 or j >= 0:
                return False

            i -= 1
            j -= 1
        return True
                    
